# .mailmap — display-only author remapping (does NOT rewrite git history).
#
# Format: <Proper Name> <proper@email> <name-to-remap> <email-to-remap>
# When the second pair is just `<email>`, all commits authored by that email
# are displayed as authored by the first pair on GitHub, in `git shortlog`,
# `git blame`, etc.
#
# Why:
# - `github-actions[bot]` shows up in the repo's Contributors sidebar from
#   merged "chore(release): version packages" PRs. The bot isn't a person and
#   shouldn't take a slot in the contributors list. Future release.yml runs
#   set git user explicitly to avoid the bot in new commits; this entry covers
#   the historical ones (v0.1.x → v0.2.x release-PR commits).

Muzaffer AŞKAR <muh.muzafferaskar@gmail.com> <41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
